# Responsive Design Standards

## Mobile-First Design Principles
All components and pages MUST implement responsive design following these established patterns from the clinic system.

## Container and Layout Standards
```tsx
// Standard page container
<div className="container mx-auto py-8 px-4 sm:px-6">

// Header layout with responsive flex
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-start sm:items-center mb-8 gap-4">

// Responsive grid layouts  
<div className="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
```

## Breakpoint Usage
- **Mobile**: Default styles (no prefix)
- **Small**: `sm:` (640px and up)
- **Medium**: `md:` (768px and up) 
- **Large**: `lg:` (1024px and up)

## Typography Responsiveness
```tsx
// Page headings
className="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold"

// Section headings  
className="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold"

// Body text remains consistent
className="text-sm text-gray-600"
```

## Button and Action Layout
```tsx
// Action button groups
<div className="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 w-full">
  <Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>
  <Button type="submit">Save</Button>
</div>
```

## Card and Component Spacing
- **Mobile**: Single column layout with full width
- **Tablet**: Two-column grid where appropriate
- **Desktop**: Three-column grid for card layouts
- **Consistent spacing**: `gap-4` for mobile, `gap-6` for larger screens

## Navigation Patterns
- **Back buttons**: Always visible and properly sized for touch
- **Breadcrumbs**: Responsive truncation on smaller screens
- **Action menus**: Convert to dropdowns on mobile when needed

## Form Responsiveness  
- **Single column** on mobile devices
- **Two-column** layout on tablets and desktop
- **Field groups** stack vertically on small screens
- **Button placement** adjusts from inline to stacked

These patterns ensure consistency with existing implementations in [app/clinic/[clinic]/clients](mdc:app/clinic/[clinic]/clients) and [app/clinic/[clinic]/orders](mdc:app/clinic/[clinic]/orders).
